<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05587</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING PRESIDENTIAL DECREE NO. 1146, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE "GOVERNMENT INSURANCE ACT OF 1977" AS AMENDED, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to address the prolonged dependence of Filipino children to their parents, due to the passing of Republic Act No.10533 or better known as the K-12 Law which mandated Filipino children to stay in school for a longer period of time.

Seeks to extend the coverage of P.D.No.1146, as amended, by extending the age of legal dependents from eighteen (18) to twenty-three (23), hence complementing the age when Filipino students normally finish their basic education and thus able to provide for themselves.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NOEL, FLORENCIO G.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-11-21</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT ENTERPRISES AND PRIVATIZATION ON 2019-11-27</td></tr></table>